text:
5 liter cask

Aroma: heavy malt - cookies, heavy hops - perfume, moderate yeast -doughy;

Appearance: fully lasting white creamy head, good lacing, hazy amber colour;

Taste: moderate to heavy bitterness, long finish;

Palate: medium to full body, dry texture, lively carbonation;

Overall:  Very complex, drank it when just opened and then finished it about two weeks later and it was still very good but less carbonated and mellower while hops kept very well. This beer kept well in refrigeration.
